The paper proposes a new family of message passing techniques for MAP estimation in graphical models, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed technique on several real-world problems, which suggests that it may be applicable to a wide range of data science problems, including computer vision (cs.CV) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves a mathematical derivation of the proposed technique, which suggests that it may be relevant to the field of data structures (cs.DS).
